itiated by the State governor Hon. Bello Matawalle. He disclosed that one of the released captives is the father of one of the 279 abducted female students of Jangebe. All the released victims looked ill, very hungry, dirty and traumatized by the terrifying experience. Vanguard News Nigeria Twenty six captives of Zamfara who fell victims of banditry have just been voluntarily handed over to the state police command by the Bandits. July 23, 2019 In "News" Their harrowing experience in the hands of armed bandits for 55 days is better imagined. Deep inside the forest where the bandits’ camp was located, the abducted women and children were kept in the open, beaten by the rain and the sun and fed with a half ration of barely… October 12, 2019 In "News" UMUAHIA—A new kidnap syndicate which says it   collects its ransom only in American   Dollars has been smashed by operatives of the Inspector- General of Police Intelligence   Response Team, in Abia State, with the arrest of five suspected members of its gang. December 13, 2017 In "News"